# 6. 荷解きの中で

Shizuku: *Exhale* Next is this room, yes?
Saito: Everything for the living room's all unpacked, but a lot of the boxes for the other rooms still haven't been opened.
Shizuku: Right, and we have all of our streaming equipment to think about... It may take us quite a bit of time to get fully organized around here.
Saito: Still... This is pretty fun. We're really getting to set up our home base like this.
Shizuku: Yes, it is! I know we're not moving in per se since we don't plan on living here or anything...
Shizuku: However, this is the start of a new chapter for us. We're still just unpacking what we need at the moment, but I'm very excited.
Saito: Hehe. Me too!
Saito: Also, we couldn't have gotten this place at a better time...
Shizuku: What do you mean?
Saito: I'll give you more details tomorrow, but the offers have been flowing in since Mr. Arimura's show aired...
Saito: So, if we hadn't found this place when we did, we probably wouldn't have had any time to go house hunting.
Shizuku: Really...?! We've been receiving that many offers?
Saito: In terms of brand-new ones, I'd say about double what we'd been receiving until now.
Saito: And on top of group offers, each of you has been receiving your own appearance offers!
Shizuku: Our own offers...?
Shizuku: I see... I suppose it's only natural for more of those to be coming in...
Saito: Is something wrong?
Shizuku: No, there's nothing wrong. It's just a small thought.
Shizuku: But I feel like we've been doing less and less streams together after we started receiving more offers to appear on our own...
Shizuku: Quite a few people have also been commenting on that lately. They'd ask where Haruka is when she's off somewhere else, or saying how they were hoping to see Minori.
Shizuku: Which is why I'm sort of worried that we're going to disappoint everyone if those kinds of things continue to happen.
Saito: Oh...
Shizuku: But I also understand that we need to keep receiving more work in order to increase our name recognition. It's become such a difficult puzzle...
Saito: Shizuku...
Saito: Yes, it is common for gaps to form between a group and their oldest fans as their fame increases...
Saito: However...
Saito: I wouldn't worry about that.
Shizuku: Wait, why not...?
Saito: Because everyone in MORE MORE JUMP! is really amazing. You, in particular, Shizuku...
Shizuku: Someone's calling. Is it your phone that's ringing, Saito...?
Saito: Oh, it might be Airi calling back about the offer she received earlier. Sorry, I need to take this!
Shizuku: (I wonder what she was going to say just now...)
Shizuku: (Still, it seems like Saito has already fully settled in as our manager.)
Shizuku: (And she hasn't actually been with us that long yet. It's truly remarkable how much we can count on her.)
Shizuku: (I mean, even when it came to finding a place to call the MORE MORE HOUSE, she found a good real estate agency while far away at home.)
Saito's Voice: Wait, right now?!
Saito's Voice: No, um... That's okay. I agree that we should discuss this in person, so... Yes, okay. I'll see you in a little bit. Bye.
Saito: Uhh... Sorry, Shizuku, but I...
Shizuku: Did something happen?
Saito: It isn't all that serious. But I'm going to need to step out for a bit to deal with something regarding this one offer Airi received.
Shizuku: Oh, I see.
Shizuku: Please, don't mind me. After all, our original plan for today was to chat, have some tea and maybe unpack a few boxes together.
Saito: *Sob* I'm really sorry! It was an absolute honor to unpack boxes with you today, Shizuku...
Saito: I promise to make time again another day! So, I hope you'll be willing to have me then!
Shizuku: Hehe. I'll be looking forward to it. Also...
Shizuku: Thank you for always doing your best for us. Please stay safe out there.
Saito: ...?!?!
Saito: Sh-Shizuku's idol smile! I couldn't have asked for a better send-off...!
Saito: This is better than any energy drink! Wish me luck! I promise to do my best!
Shizuku: Yes, good luck!
Shizuku: Hehe. She's so funny when she gets all excited like that...
Shizuku: Anyway...
Shizuku: It's still too early to go home, so I think I'll do a little more unpacking before I do.
Shizuku: Airi said that I didn't have to worry about any of the equipment, so I'll try sorting out our home décor and...
???: <Oh, perfect! Shizuku's here!>
Shizuku: Huh?
Shizuku: Rin? Luka...?
Shizuku: You two sound very excited about something. May I ask what?
Luka: <There's something we need you to see right now, Shizuku.>
Rin: <Yeah, you gotta come over to SEKAI!>
Shizuku: What...?
